The best way to save some power is to turn it off. Some battery backed games like Fire Emblem and Just Breed have a "suspend" mode, it doesn't actually save the game, but it just allow you to turn the power off and continue the stage later, but this isn't a save scince you can't restore it if the game is over.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Sun Mar 13, 2005 10:02 am</p><hr />
